<TITLE> First woman appointed as Dhaka district & session's judge </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 11 (bdnews24.com)  Krishna Debnath, an administrative tribunal member, was appointed on Monday as the first ever women judge of Dhaka district and sessions judge's court since its establishment over 150 years ago. Krishna formally assumed her office on Monday after a law ministry circular was served in this concern earlier in the day. Krishna is the daughter of the late judge Dinesh Chandra Debnath and current president of the Bangladesh Women Judges Association. She also will be an ex-officio president of the Bangladesh Judicial Services Association. bdnew
